  "prompt": "Do employees at Select Income REIT have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "As of my last update, specific information about work-life balance at Select Income REIT (now part of Industrial Logistics Properties Trust following a merger) isn't readily available in detail. Work-life balance can vary widely in any company depending on the department, role, and even individual managers. Generally, roles in property management, finance, or operations may have different demands that affect work-life balance.\n\nOffice-based roles might offer more predictable hours compared to site-based positions, which can sometimes demand irregular hours due to the nature of property management. Additionally, the company's policies on work-life balance can shift over time, particularly following mergers or under new management.\n\nFor the most accurate and current insights, it would be useful to look at employee reviews on websites like Glassdoor or Indeed, where you can find recent employee feedback on work-life balance. Furthermore, reaching out to current or former employees through professional networking sites like LinkedIn could provide more anecdotal insights into the work-life balance within specific roles and departments at the company.",
